<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Xzarann</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-01 02:51:06</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is an awesome ring. One of the best for those BIG race tanks. Reason being, ogres, trolls, and barbarians have enough str to spare. So why waste a finger slot to add more? I would suggest going with a pair of these rings. They add a total of 10 AC, plus an extra 110 HPs. The thing is, I am not a large raced warrior. :) Therefore, I am stuck not being able to use this fine ring and forced to use a str ring in its place, just so I wont be encumbered my entire life! Now if you think... 110hps, that isnt much. Then think about it this way...An ogre warrior starts out with a base of 140 str. That is nearly enough for two small race warriors! So much extra, that a smart warrior would dump all points into Agi or Dex instead of more Str. Why waste space adding more str when you have plenty already? Put these rings on along with a Skull Shaped Barbute (13 ac, Plus 35 HP, plus 10 Sv Magic) and that is in total: Plus 145hp, Plus 23 AC. Then if you are a Warrior as I am, add a Crafted BP and you have an extra 25 HPs added to total 170hps. Once you start to add all of these small things up, you have one thing...A better tank! A tank is there to take blows. What better to help him do that than an extra 23 AC and 145-170hps? That last extra hit these extra hps allow may be the one just before your cleric is able to throw you a Superior Heal as you pull the mob off of them. All of the little items add up when put together and if I could start over from a lvl 32 human warrior to a lvl 1 ogre I would! Truth is I am too lazy to earn all of those levels back. Would rather be doing that on my druid or wizard. So, to all of those ogres, trolls and Barbarians...Get a pair of these ASAP. It makes you able to perform your job better and easier.<BR>
<BR>
Xzarann Xecutionist<BR>
Warrior of the 32nd Scar<BR>
Brethren of the Wolf<BR>
Karana Server<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
