<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Des</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-24 23:59:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> A little info for people who have never tried any trade skills. The cost of the materials are not what you are paying for. You are paying for the time and investment the jeweler has put into getting a skill up. Not only the time the jeweler has lost in fighting mobs to get the money to buy the materials, but the money lost in failures which are much higher than anyone would like to know. I spent 10k to get my skill to 195. Also lost 3k in one night to Plat failures. Be aware of the costs to the jeweler before you get rude when quoted a price. If you are looking for a particular item look it up first and know exactly what you want and the price range it goes for. Most jewelers are not out to make a fortune, just a little in return for their time and efforts. If you do not like the price say something like I would like to shop around a little more but I may get back to you. Saying things like You charge too much and what if I buy the materials will you make it for me just isn't right. I will not make jewelry in return for the materials. If I fail what am I supposed to do go buy more materials and spend over 200pp in some cases to try to make another? Please be informed of the costs involved before you start degrading another player who is doing something that will help you out in the long run.</font></td></tr></table>
